Sentencas: This work is one of the first attempts of using focused ion beam/lift-out (FIB/lift-out) techniques to prepare TEM specimens containing electrode/electrolyte interfaces in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Microstructure degradation of an anode/electrolyte interface in SOFC studied by transmission electron microscopy

Sentencas: The present specimen was made from an Ni+YSZ (anode)/YSZ (electrolyte) half-cell which has undergone a long-term testing at a temperature of 850 degreesC over 1800 h in H-2 with 1% to 3% H2O under an anodic load of 300 mA cm(-2).
Titulo: Microstructure degradation of an anode/electrolyte interface in SOFC studied by transmission electron microscopy

Sentencas: The microstructure and phase chemistry in the interfacial region was analyzed using a JEM-3000F and EDS with a lateral resolution of nanometers.
Titulo: Microstructure degradation of an anode/electrolyte interface in SOFC studied by transmission electron microscopy

Sentencas: The impurity phase accumulated at the interface seen earlier by SEM have been characterized.
Titulo: Microstructure degradation of an anode/electrolyte interface in SOFC studied by transmission electron microscopy

Sentencas: It is a silicate glass with an amorphous structure and a composition of similar to90 mol% SiO2 as well as a few percent of Na2O,CaO, ZrO2, V2O3 etc.
Titulo: Microstructure degradation of an anode/electrolyte interface in SOFC studied by transmission electron microscopy

Sentencas: The silicate glass phase is distributed as films of nanoscale along the anode/electrolyte interface and Ni/YSZ grain boundaries.
Titulo: Microstructure degradation of an anode/electrolyte interface in SOFC studied by transmission electron microscopy

Sentencas: Its influence on the microstructural degradation of the interfacial region is evaluated.
Titulo: Microstructure degradation of an anode/electrolyte interface in SOFC studied by transmission electron microscopy

Sentencas: The FIB/lift-out techniques have been shown to be viable for specimen preparation from SOFC interface.
Titulo: Microstructure degradation of an anode/electrolyte interface in SOFC studied by transmission electron microscopy
